        " اَلْمَاءِ فَمَاتَتْ أَ تُؤْكَلُ قَالَ \"لاَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4153 - Hammad narrated from Abu Ayyub that he asked Abu Abdillah (as) about a man who caught a fish, tied it with a string, and released it into the water, and then it died.\nImam (as) said: \"It should not be eaten.\""
        ]
      }
